SIMPLE: spright
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spright
<hw>Spright</hw> <pr>(spr⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Sprite</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Spirit; mind; soul; state of
mind; mood.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧The high heroic
<xex>spright</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wondrous great grief groweth in my <qex>spright</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A supernatural being; a spirit; a shade; an
apparition; a ghost.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> sprite.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Forth he called, out of deep darkness dread,⟦br⟧
Legions of <qex>sprights</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To thee, O Father, Son, and Sacred <qex>Spright</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Fairfax.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A kind of short arrow.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spright</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Spright
<hw>Spright</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To haunt, as a spright.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sprightful</ent>⟦br⟧
